<span class="thumb thumb--square"><span class="thumb__sizer"><span class="thumb__tugger"><img alt="" class=" thumb__image" play="false" src="https://pi.tedcdn.com/r/pe.tedcdn.com/images/ted/1441_253x190.jpg?" /><span class="thumb__aligner"></span></span></span></span>
</a>
<div class='talk-speaker__details media__message'>
<div class='talk-speaker__name h10'>
<a class="l3 talk-speaker__link" href="/speakers/ashraf_ghani">Ashraf Ghani</a>
</div>
<div class='talk-speaker__description'>
President-elect of Afghanistan
</div>
<div class='talk-speaker__bio'>
Ashraf Ghani, Afghanistanâ€™s new president-elect, and his opponent, Abdullah Abdullah, will share power in a national unity government. He previously served as Finance Minister and as a chancellor of Kabul University.
<a class="l3 talk-speaker__link" href="/speakers/ashraf_ghani">Full bio</a>
</div>
